cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.SI

This paper deals with predictive analytics and machine learning techniques to infer people's characteristics from behavioral data. The paper focuses on feature selection based on causal identification to improve the accuracy of predictions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also deals with data privacy and security, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses data from a theme park, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
